                "invention-title": [
                    "Method and device for preparing hydrogenated semiconductor material at normal temperature through low-energy hydrogen plasma and application",
                    "一种低能氢等离子体常温制备氢化半导体材料的方法、装置及应用"
                ]
            },
            "abstract": [
                {
                    "p": "The invention relates to the technical field of semiconductor material surface engineering, in particular to a method and device for preparing a hydrogenated semiconductor material at normal temperature through low-energy hydrogen plasma and application. The electromagnetic coil is added around the sample table to generate magnetic lines, increase the density of hydrogen ions, reduce the power for starting hydrogen plasma and generate low-energy hydrogen ions, then the hydrogen ions are accelerated to the surface of a semiconductor by adopting low voltage, and the penetration depth of the hydrogen ions can be controlled to be 0.1-2nm, so that the generation of body defects and recombination centers is avoided, and the quality of the semiconductor is improved. Room-temperature controllable hydrogenation is realized, and uniform and large-area hydrogenated semiconductor materials can be prepared in batches."
                },
                {
                    "p": "本发明涉及半导体材料表面工程技术领域，主要是一种低能氢等离子体常温制备氢化半导体材料的方法、装置及应用。本发明在样品台周围添加电磁线圈来产生磁力线，增加氢离子的密度，降低启动氢等离子体的功率，产生低能氢离子，然后采用低电压来加速氢离子到半导体表面，能够将氢离子渗透深度控制在0.1～2nm，从而避免产生体缺陷和复合中心，实现了室温可控氢化，能够批量制备均匀、大面积的氢化半导体材料。"
                }
            ]
